---
title: Cherry Balsamic Chicken with Almond Couscous & Roasted Broccoli
description: Over here, we believe chicken is a canvas, and we like to paint it with allllll the flavors. Tonight’s palette: A saucy coating that includes glossy cherry jam and balsamic pan sauce—because why choose one of these ingredients when you could both? Add to that a side of almond-studded couscous and roasted carrots, and you have yourself a dinner to Remem-brandt (see what we did there?).
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/646464f28ab1333a8ca2506a-c2c8f9bb.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/650ad075f209a4fa36352f03.pdf
author: HelloFresh
nutrition:
  calories: 700 kcal
  fat: 38 g
  saturated fat: 14 g
  carbohydrates: 51 g
  sugar: 15 g
  protein: 42 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 310 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/cherry-balsamic-chicken-650ad075f209a4fa36352f03
cuisine: North America
course: main course
servings: 2
time required: 35 minutes
---

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%ounce} on a diagonal into
½-inch-thick pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. (Save carrots for another use.)

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @sliced almonds{1/2%ounce};
cook, stirring, until lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add garlic, @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce}, and a pinch of @salt{}; cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in ¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings) and cover. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat
to low. Simmer, covered, until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Drain any excess water from
pot if necessary.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{5%teaspoon},
@salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on middle rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> Swap in broccoli for carrots; roast 15-20 minutes.

While carrots roast, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with paper towels; season generously
all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and
cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook
for ~{1%minute}.

Add @white balsamic vinegar{1}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @cherry jam{1}, and ¼ cup water
(1/3 cup for 4 servings); whisk to combine. Bring to a simmer and cook until thickened,
~{1-2%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

Stir @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) into #pot{} with couscous; season with salt and pepper.

Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

Divide couscous, chicken, and carrots between plates. Top chicken with sauce. Garnish with
scallion greens and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165º.